Here at Skedulo, we’re on a mission to support the 2.7 billion people in the
world and the companies that employ them who do not work at a desk every day.
Our global teams are collaborative, ambitious, innovative, and passionate
about helping our customers realize their fullest potential by enabling their
mobile workforces.

The Skedulo team is a tight-knit group of builders who are passionate about
shaping the future of how work gets done outside of the traditional office
setting. We are looking for motivated, self-starters who share our values,
challenge the status quo, and push the pace of innovation in order to
accelerate growth. If you’re drawn to solving hard problems and want to help
develop software that will make a difference in people’s lives, Skedulo is for
you. Visit our website to learn more about what Skedulo does and to learn more
about our people and team.

The Core Services team builds the underpinning components and services of our
product platform These services are the “glue” that binds the rest of the
product together.The Engineering Manager for the Core Services team is
accountable for leading the Core Services team of engineers to design,
implement, and maintain critical infrastructure, and ensuring the reliability
and scalability of our core services under their remit.

The Engineering Manager leads the execution of large cycles of work and
complex initiatives across their team and is responsible for meeting technical
objectives, alongside some hands-on software development and contributions to
the codebase.

This role is accountable for leading customer and operational escalation
responses for their team and ensuring their team is aware and aligned on
customer and business commitments. They will work within their team to ensure
PIRs and their associated action items are completed for all customer outage
events.

The Engineering Manager is responsible for building a high-performing team and
ensuring that they are enabled to succeed. They are a custodian of staff
development and morale while ensuring that the teams are resourced and
delivering for our customers. They will be coaching and mentoring their direct
reports. They are a guide for reports on their career journeys as well as
aligning expectations, maintaining morale, and facilitating one-on-ones all
while providing positive and constructive feedback.

** RESPONSIBILITIES **

** Delivery and Execution **

· Provide technical leadership and guidance to the Core Services team,
fostering a culture of innovation, collaboration, and excellence to
consistently deliver business impact

· Responsible for Core Services engineering delivery inline with the roadmap;
accountable for the performance of the team and the results they deliver

· Consistently meet commitments and timelines agreed by the company and the
Core Services team

· Collaborate and partner with Engineering teams, Product leaders and other
stakeholders across Skedulo to ensure the timely delivery of shared business
objectives and dependencies

· Ensure the Core Services team outcomes are aligned with the wider business
strategy

· Contribute to Roadmap planning and tactical work planning for the Core
Services Group

· Oversee the planning and execution of projects related to core services,
including resource allocation, timelines, and deliverables

· Build strong relationships with Engineering leaders across the business and
effectively navigate organizational dynamics and changes

· Demonstrate strong decision-making skills in ambiguous situations, balancing
data-driven analysis, stakeholder input, and a sense of urgency to make
informed choices that drive progress

· Contributing to code and code reviews and helping the team deliver robust,
maintainable, and high-quality software. Our tech stack consists of React,
Typescript, Kotlin, Node, and Scala. Familiarity with some but not all of
these technologies is required.

** People Leadership **

· Recruit, mentor, develop, and retain high performing engineering talent to
execute the company's technical vision.

· Help your staff to overcome obstacles, resolve blockers, and complete work
tasks

\- Mentor/ coach direct reports in an open, respectful, flexible, and
empathetic manner

· Provide positive and constructive feedback to direct reports in a timely
manner

· Work with your reports to build and achieve goals on their Career
Development Plans through regular (weekly or bi-weekly) 1 on 1’s with your
direct reports.

· Partner with other Engineering leaders to ensure adequate resourcing

· Participate in the performance management process where required

· Share relevant information from senior leaders and executives to your staff
and communicate with your team in an effective, clear, concise manner in both
written and verbal form

· Drive high performance across your team with even distribution of
performance (vs. hero-culture)

· Weave our company values into the fabric of how your team operates and makes
decisions

· Can clearly articulate the company vision and how your team supports the
vision

· Demonstrate self-awareness, accountability, ownership and strong
communication when issues arise

· Effectively delegate and promote autonomy with situational support

· Actively limit single points of failure and knowledge silos

· Provide clarity around the processes and policies of Skedulo for your staff

· Care genuinely for the health and wellbeing of your staff

** Process Improvement **

· Drive initiatives across your Group and more broadly across Engineering to
continuously improve the security, observability, availability, and
performance of the Skedulo product suite

** MINIMUM REQUIREMENTS **

· Must have at least 5+ years commercial experience in software development.

· Must have at least 2+ years prior experience in a people leadership role.

· Must have at least 2+ years working with agile development methodologies.

** PREFERRED REQUIREMENTS **

· Ability to think quickly, and work well in an agile environment.

· Possess strong communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to
collaborate effectively with cross-functional teams and contribute to the
product strategy to successfully deliver on the product roadmap

· Possess strong verbal, and written English communication skills with the
ability to explain the approach to all levels of the organization including
key stakeholders

· Prior experience and comfort in managing teams while, at the same time,
setting goals, giving context and empowering people to achieve those goals

· Strong project management, problem-solving, and decision-making skills

